Multiple award-winning songstress, Tems has featured on the soundtrack for Black Panther 2 trailer. The official teaser for Marvel Studios’ “Black Panther: Wakanda Forever”, released on Sunday, sees the super star give a sonorous rendition of Bob Marley’s “No woman, no cry.” Kendrick Lamar’s “Alright” was also featured on the soundtrack. In the trailer, the song plays until halfway through where the part “Everything’s gonna be alright” plays with Kendrick Lamar’s “We gon’ be alright”, before the latter continues till the end.   BBNaija: What will happen if Chichi and I align – Hermes     Tiwa Savage gushes over Tobi Amusan in surprise video call     #BBNaija: Sheggz justifies peeping at Chichi during bath   Tem’s manager, Muyiwa Awoniyi sharing the trailer via his Twitter handle said: “Grateful to the amazing people at @MarvelStudios. BIG LOVE to the legend Ryan Coogler. “It’s @temsbaby on the official Black Panther 2 trailer. My father in heaven. Thank you once again. Rest in peace @chadwickboseman.” Black Panther 2 trailer stars Lupita Nyong’o, Angela Bassett, Letitia Wright, Danai Gurira, Winston Duke, among others.